https://realpython.com/blog/python/vim-and-python-a-match-made-in-heaven/#vim-extensions

* Get Vundle extension manager
  $ git clone https://github.com/gmarik/Vundle.vim.git ~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim

* Copy .vimrc
  $ cp .vimrc  ~/

* Search .vimrc for "TODO lines to check if something extra is required!

* Then open vim and run: 
  :PluginInstall


-------------------------------------------
* Install powerline (useful for other "programs" like tmux, i3
  $ pip install --user powerline-status psutil

* Add/export $(python -m site --user-base) path to PATH

* Install powerline fonts with:
  $sudo apt-get install fonts-powerline
